sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Deletes a traffic manager profile.

Inputs :

  • Subscription ID - Unique ID of the subscription.
  • Resource Group - Name of the resource group.
  • Profile Name - Name of the traffic manager profile.

Outputs :

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Azure Traffic Manager, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Invalid Credentials.
  • Invalid Subscription.

To use this action, the corresponding Azure Traffic Manager connection and credential must be created and associated with the Azure Traffic Manager Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
